As most know my grandpops passed away last thurs. You taught me and my cousins as well as my aunts & uncles so many things. I remember sitting on the kitchen table and you showing me how to tie my shoes, fishing at the lake, going painting with you, finding out I was deathly allergic to cats, putting you van in nuetral and rolling away, planting an apple tree in your yard, watching walker texas ranger, country music, flying to see you from Texas, your train sets & that you gotta have something to wash it down. I could go on all day about things I learned from you and things we did. You'll be missed but never forgotten. Your back with grandma now though and I know you both are watching over us all.

Their commitment to rugby and the brotherhood that ties us all together, both on and off the pitch is characterized by the permanent smiles that they carry on their faces!
Please join us in celebrating these 2 individuals achievements so far, and wish them great success as they compete on the National stage this weekend. All the best to Chris, Stevie and all Toes playing this weekend!
